title: #NCAAVB: #14 Cats fall in four-set affair at 6th ranked Dawgs
text:
#NCAAVB: #14 Cats fall in four-set affair at 6th ranked Dawgs - Tucson News Now Member Center: #NCAAVB: #14 Cats fall in four-set affair at 6th ranked Dawgs Posted: dkelly@tucsonnewsnow.com SEATTLE, WA - 
Despite a decisive first-set victory, No. 14 Arizona volleyball fell in four sets to the sixth-ranked Washington Huskies (25-17, 22-25, 25-27, 17-25) on Wednesday evening at the Alaska Airlines Arena). 
Kalei Mau picked up her sixth 20-plus kill outing in Arizona's last 10 matches with 23 to lead all scorers. 
Penina Snuka posted her fourth consecutive double-double with 46 assists and 13 digs. The junior added two kills and two aces. 
McKenna Painton posted a career-high 18 digs in the match. UA outdug the Huskies 62-60. 
Arizona had no answer for the Washington presence at the net. Washington outblocked Arizona 13-6, while middle blocker Lianna Sybeldon posted 19 kills on an errorless 26 swings (.731). 
The loss was Arizona's fifth to a team currently ranked in the top 10. Arizona has taken at least set in each of the five matches, including a pair of five set losses to No. 2 Texas and No. 7 Stanford. In addition to Arizona's seven set victories over top-10 teams, UA has forced deuce in six additional sets. Arizona is 0-6 in those sets. 
Arizona is 12-0 against teams ranked outside of the top nine in the current AVCA Top 25, a record that will be put to the test on Friday when the Cats take on a 12-4 Washington State team in Pullman. 
Up Next: The Wildcats hit the road for four matches beginning in Washington. Arizona takes on the Huskies on Wednesday, Oct. 7 at 7:30 p.m. before heading to Corvallis to take on Washington State on Friday, Oct. 9 at 6 p.m. MST. Both matches will be televised by the Pac-12 Networks.
